To all the vets:<br>
     April 30, 1975 was my first birthday.  I am the son of a Vietnam vet and I wanted to take a moment to thank you all.  I have the deepest respect for any person who would serve their country, especially in a time of such great difficulty.  Doc Spatz, from what I read on the other thread, I give you credit for your convictions too.  Not all of today's young people are ignorant and ungrateful.  For what it is worth, Welcome Home to all of you!  God Bless you all!  In May 1985, I was on the sidelines of the New York ticker tape parade for Vietnam veterans and saluted them all, today I still do the same for all of you.  Let Vietnam be a badge of honor and not a burden that all you carry (I might be unknowing of what Vietnam was really like, but a well wish anyway). Also, I hope that April 30 is not the fall of this site.  I'm new here, so I'll read the back posts before I post again.  I'm trying to understand the war my father fought in too.   I'm a elementary school teacher and on April 30, I will have the kids do a tribute to Vietnam Vets.  I know they're very young, but not to young not to be thankful.  Best Wishes   
<p><code>--   (Joseph-Grateful 23 year old) </code><p>


